			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Scrolls for Erudin</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=121456"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:autumnwind@bellsouth.net">Caralda Autumnwind</a> | 
		                        4/25/2000 5:16:18 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Barnal Flamehand says 'And a fine day to you too Caralda. What is it that brings you here? Fortune? Adventure? In either case it will be more fun then the duty I have. I am to acquire what scrolls I can for the High Council of Erudin. And your also in luck, as I seek the services of a mighty adventurer like yourself. Do you wish to [aid me in my duty?]<BR>
<BR>
You say, 'I will aid you in your duty.'<BR>
<BR>
Barnal Flamehand says 'Then you will do this for me. Venture beyond this outpost, to the farthest lands and darkest dungeons. Within them the creatures with the greatest power will have scrolls. The residents here will be able to give you general locations of the most dangerous places. I wish to have returned to me the scroll of Atol's Spectral Shackles, the scroll Tears of Druzzil, the scroll Inferno of AlKabor, and lastly the scroll Pillar of Lightning. Make haste as the High Council cannot be kept waiting and I shall [reward] you. <BR>
<BR>
You say, 'What reward?'<BR>
<BR>
Barnal Flamehand says 'I am not empty handed. In that I have already located some of the most rare scrolls. I'll part with one of my four for what you return to me. Fare the well! <BR>

			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
